Problem: How many positive whole-number divisors does 196 have?
Solution: 196 is 2 x 2 x 7 x 7. That is 2 2 times and 7 2 times. The number of positive whole number divisors is ( 2 + 1 )( 2 + 1 ) ( 2 times 7 times ) = (3)(3) = 27.
196 has 27 positive whole-number divisors.
